            <thetext>Patches to Cyrus IMAP and documentation that enable two new configuration options,
notifymail and notifysieve. These two options allows the user to select at
runtime which notify service he wants to be used, from {none,daemon,zephyr}.
Zephyr support is available if --with-zephyr is specified  to configure. daemon
is notify_unix.c, and it is always available. none is no notification service.

The selection of notification service does NOT interfere with the snmp
statistics (including the none selection).

Patch sent to the cyrus imapd ML, url is to archive of said ML.</thetext>
